'''Parvaresh–Vardy codes''' are a family of [[error-correcting code]]s first described in 2005 by Farzad Parvaresh and [[Alexander Vardy]].<ref name="pv05">{{cite journal|last=Parvaresh|first=Farzad|author2=Alexander Vardy|title=Correcting Errors Beyond the Guruswami-Sudan Radius in Polynomial Time|journal=Proceedings of the 2005 46th Annual IEEE Symposium on Foundations of Computer Science (FOCS'05)|date=October 2005|pages=285–294|doi=10.1109/SFCS.2005.29|isbn=0-7695-2468-0}}</ref> They can be used for efficient [[list-decoding]].

