{{Uniform hyperbolic tiles db|Uniform hyperbolic tiling stat table|U74_02}}
In [[geometry]], the '''rhombitetraheptagonal tiling''' is a uniform tiling of the [[Hyperbolic geometry|hyperbolic plane]]. It has [[Schläfli symbol]] of rr{4,7}. It can be seen as constructed as a [[Rectification (geometry)|rectified]] [[tetraheptagonal tiling]], r{7,4}, as well as an [[Expansion (geometry)|expanded]] [[order-4 heptagonal tiling]] or expanded [[order-7 square tiling]].

== Dual tiling ==
The dual is called the ''deltoidal tetraheptagonal tiling'' with [[face configuration]] V.4.4.4.7.
:[[File:Deltoidal_tetraheptagonal_til.png|240px]]

